# useEffect Business Logic Comments

For `useEffect` hooks that implement non-trivial business logic, add a brief comment above the effect explaining **what** it does and **why** (the business rule or user-facing behavior).

## When to Add Comments

- Effects that sync UI with external state (Redux, URL, etc.)
- Effects that handle side effects on mount/unmount or when deps change
- Effects that implement domain rules (e.g. "stop playback when leaving results view")
- Effects with cleanup logic

## When to Skip

- Trivial effects (e.g. single `document.title` assignment)
- Effects whose purpose is obvious from the code

## Format

Place a 1–2 line comment immediately above the `useEffect`:

```typescript
// Stop callstack playback when user leaves results view on mobile (Back button).
useEffect(() => {
  if (prevView === "results" && currentView !== "results") {
    dispatch(callstackSlice.actions.setIsPlaying(false));
  }
}, [currentView, prevView, dispatch]);
```

## Example

```typescript
// Show snackbar when progress is non-null; hide when null. Single source of truth for this snackbar.
useEffect(() => {
  if (progress !== null) {
    if (!hasSnackbarShownRef.current) {
      hasSnackbarShownRef.current = true;
      enqueueSnackbar(<ProgressContent />, { key: SNACKBAR_KEY });
    }
  } else {
    if (hasSnackbarShownRef.current) {
      hasSnackbarShownRef.current = false;
      closeSnackbar(SNACKBAR_KEY);
    }
  }
}, [progress, enqueueSnackbar, closeSnackbar]);
```
